Changing Permission and Ownership:
---------------------------------
View permission: "ls -ls"
Change permission: "chmod [options] [permission] file"
Change Owner: chown user file


Topic:6
$: This is normal user with limited permissions
#: Super user/root user with all permissions

To convert normal user to super/root user: "sudo su"

Topic:7 copy, move or rename files and directories
---------------------------------------------------
1.copy commands(cp)
	.cp raju shiva
	
2.copy file to directory
	.cp shiva /path/to/dir
	.cp shiva /home/ec2-user/nexgen
	
3.copy Multiple files
	.cp dinesh naresh raju /home/ec2-user/nexgen
	
4.Move a file
	.mv shiva /home/ec2-user/nexgen

5.Move a directory
	.mv nexgen /home/ec2-user/yash/priya

6.Rename commands(mv)
Linux does not have a separate rename command; mv is used for renaming

rename a file:
	.mv oldname newname
	
remove a directory(old)
